  <title>2.3 Part-Editor</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Editor<keyword>Part</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Part-Editor</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">2.3 Part-Editor</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;"><image src="2r.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text>Part-Editor </para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-WhatisGeometryUsedfor">Why edit a Part?</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Use the <text styleclass="Interface2">Part-Editor </text>to:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Edit the <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">length of a </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text>&#32;</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Add sketch-elements to <text styleclass="Element-Header">Parts</text> and the <text styleclass="Element-Header">Base-Part</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Add dimensions to or between sketch-elements</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Add constraints to or between sketch-elements</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">When you edit a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text>, the <text styleclass="Interface2">Part-Editor</text> replaces the <text styleclass="Interface2">Mechanism-Editor</text> in which the <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text> is a child.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">To edit a different <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text>, you must close the <text styleclass="Interface2">Part-Editor</text>, and then edit the different <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Part-Editor workspace</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="1" style="cell-padding:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-PART-EDITOR-EX.ipp" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Part-Editor: Example]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Graphics-area</text><text styleclass="VariableName-indent"> : </text>shows sketch-elements, dimensions, Part-Axes.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Toolbars</text> : are to the left and right of the graphics-area. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Name-tabs</text> : are above the graphics-area. The name of the tab changes from the name of the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text> to the name of the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Menus and Toolbars:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Geometry menu:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><image src="MD-17-Menu-Geometry.ipp" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Geometry menu : Add sketch-elements and constraints]]></caption></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="T_Menu">Geometry menu</text> has commands to add sketch-elements to a <text styleclass="Element-Header">Part</text> and add constraints to, or between, the sketch-elements<text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Two toolbars:</para>
          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2"><text styleclass="VariableName">Geometry toolbar</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">(left (&lt;&lt;) of graphics-area)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Add sketch-elements and dimensions with these commands in the Geometry menu and <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Geometry" styleclass="SeeAlso">Geometry toolbar</link><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2"><text styleclass="VariableName">Constraints toolbar</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">(right (&gt;&gt;) of graphics-area)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Add constraints to, and between, sketch-elements with these commands in the Geometry menu and <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Constraints" styleclass="SeeAlso">Constraints toolbar</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
